Coord_trans()

Notes:

ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) +
  geom_jitter(alpha = 1/20) +
  xlim(13,90)

Look up the documentation for coord_trans() and add a layer to the plot that transforms friend_count using the square root function. Create your plot!

ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) +
  geom_point(alpha = 1/20, position = position_jitter(h=0)) +
  xlim(13,90) +
  coord_trans(y = 'sqrt')
## Warning: Removed 5173 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

Overlaying Summaries with Raw Data

Notes: Overlaying the mean friend line over the scatter plot of data.

ggplot(aes(x=age, y=friend_count), data=pf) +
  geom_point(alpha = .05,
             position = position_jitter(h=0),
             color='orange') +
  coord_trans(y='sqrt') +
  geom_line(stat='summary', fun.y=mean) + 
  geom_line(stat='summary', fun.y=quantile, fun.args=list(probs=.1), linetype =2, color ='blue') +
    geom_line(stat='summary', fun.y=quantile, fun.args=list(probs=.9), linetype =2, color ='blue') +
      geom_line(stat='summary', fun.y=quantile, fun.args=list(probs=.5), color ='blue') +
  coord_cartesian(xlim=c(13,90), ylim=c(0,1000))

Correlation on Subsets

Notes:

Subset the users equal or less than 70 before running the correlation.

with(subset(pf, age <= 70), cor.test(age,friend_count, method='pearson'))

Understanding Noise: Age to Age Months

Notes:

pf$age_with_months <- pf$age + (12 - pf$dob_month) / 12

Age with Months Means

Using dplyr to group users by age_with_months, and summarize the information.

library(dplyr)

pf.fc_by_age_months <- pf %>%
  group_by(age_with_months) %>%
  summarise(friend_count_mean = mean(friend_count),
            friend_count_median = median(friend_count),
            n=n()) %>%
  arrange(age_with_months)

head(pf.fc_by_age_months)
## # A tibble: 6 x 4
##   age_with_months friend_count_mean friend_count_median     n
##             <dbl>             <dbl>               <dbl> <int>
## 1        13.16667          46.33333                30.5     6
## 2        13.25000         115.07143                23.5    14
## 3        13.33333         136.20000                44.0    25
## 4        13.41667         164.24242                72.0    33
## 5        13.50000         131.17778                66.0    45
## 6        13.58333         156.81481                64.0    54

Programming Assignment

Noise in Conditional Means

ggplot(data=pf.fc_by_age_months, aes(x=age_with_months, y=friend_count_mean)) +
  geom_line() +
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0,71))

Smoothing Conditional Means

Notes:

ggplot(data=pf.fc_by_age_months, aes(x=age_with_months, y=friend_count_mean)) +
  geom_line() +
  coord_cartesian(xlim = c(0,71)) +
  geom_smooth()
